                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Mr. William Tent, of Sweet<lb></lb>ing's-rents, Royal Exchange. The prisoner came into the shop on the 1st</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183810220021"></xptr>
               <p>of October, and asked for some black worsted gloves—while I turned to get them he took a satin scarf off the counter and put it under his coat—I saw him do it—my master came in, and I saw the prisoner go to the bottom of the shop and take nine handkerchiefs—I told him to put them down—he threw them down and ran out—I ran and took him, and asked him to put down the scarf—he dropped it, and said he had not been in the shop—it was dropped at the corner of Thread needle-street—I did not see him drop it.</p>
